        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " : “And the Couriers stood.” By “the people,” the chronicler obviously means, not the mass of the congregation, but the armed body who were to “compass the king round about, every man with his weapons in his hand” (",
        "children": []
