  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 10.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "All",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "the people; i.e.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "the people; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "accented",
            "text": "i.e.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", again, all those, not being Levites and priests, who had been trusted to assist. The parallel (ver. 11) summarizes them under the name ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "the guard.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " It may be just noted, in passing, that, while the Hebrew text has in both places \"shoulder,\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " for the \"side\" of this verse, and the \"corner\" of the parallel, the Revised Version has harmonized the rendering, electing the rendering ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "side. From the right side of the temple to the left side.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "side. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cmt_word",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "From the right side of the temple to the left side.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " This is equivalent to saying, those composing the guard were placed on the south and north sides. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Along by the altar",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This was the altar of burnt offerings in front of the perch, and close by which the young \"king stood at his pillar,\" or on his ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "pedestal",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (ver. 13), the rows of the guard bristling with weapons before and behind and round about him. 2 Chronicles 23:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The account of the occupation of the temple thus arranged agrees with ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 11:9-11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Instead of המּאות שׂרי (Kings), in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 23:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " are very fittingly named \"the Levites (as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 23:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") and all Judah,\" viz., in its chiefs, since the high priest had assured himself of the support of the heads of the fathers'-houses of Israel (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 23:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Further, to the statement that those who were departing from the service also took part in the affair, it is added, \"for Jehoiada had not dismissed the courses.\" המּחלקות are the divisions which, according to the arrangement made by David (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 24-26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), had charge of the temple service at that time. To the captains Jehoiada gave the spears and shields which had been presented to the temple by David as offerings, because they had come into the temple without weapons; see on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 11:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ויּעמד, \"and he caused the whole people to take position,\" is connected formally with ויּתּן, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 23:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; while in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 11:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", we have simply ויּעמדוּ. ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
]